-- Fink Sees ’Bright’ U.S. Economy With Growth of 2.5% to 2.8%
-- B y   S r e e   V i d y a   B h a k t a v a t s a l a m
-- 2012-04-18T13:37:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/fink-sees-bright-u-s-economy-with-growth-of-2-5-to-2-8-.html
BlackRock Inc. (BLK) ’s Chief Executive
Officer Laurence D. Fink said he sees the United States as a
“bright spot” in the global economy with growth of 2.5 percent
to 2.8 percent this year.  In Europe, the European Central Bank will have to ease
monetary policy to stimulate growth, Fink said today in a
conference call with investors and analysts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
